supplier_info.dropoff_instructions:
After collecting your luggage, please call our phone number to arrange your shuttle pick-up on on 07 3006 7442 and International Dialling: +61 7 3006 7442. If you are unable to reach us by phone, proceed directly to the shuttle pick-up point. 

For International Bookings: From the arrivals hall, turn left and walk past the Coffee Club. Continue straight ahead towards the exit doors located in the far corner of the terminal. Exit the terminal and head down the ramp to your left, following the pathway to the end of the covered walkway. Cross the pedestrian crossing and wait at shuttle bay 3/4 for the Goldcar shuttle. 

For Domestic Bookings: From the baggage claim area, exit the terminal through the main doors. Walk towards the skywalk and proceed up the travelator. At the top of the travelator, turn left and walk across the skywalk to the second travelator on your right. Exit the terminal, walk across the Skywalk and go down the travelator to B1/B2 on the ground floor. Please wait here for the Goldcar shuttle to collect you.

messages.content:
Here are the price comparisons for renting a car at Brisbane Airport for a day, with pick-up times at 10 AM on two different days:

### 1. Pick-up on November 22, 2024
- **Car Model**: MG 3 (Compact)
- **Price**: $39.83 USD
- **Supplier**: Bargain Car Rentals
- **Features**: 
  - Unlimited mileage
  - Automatic transmission
  - Free cancellation
- **Rating**: 8.0 (Very good based on 3,243 reviews)

### 2. Pick-up on November 23, 2024
- **Car Model**: MG HS (Standard)
- **Price**: $44.02 USD
- **Supplier**: Bargain Car Rentals
- **Features**: 
  - Unlimited mileage
  - Automatic transmission
  - Free cancellation
- **Rating**: 8.0 (Very good based on 3,243 reviews)

### Summary of Price Differences
- **November 22, 2024**: $39.83 USD
- **November 23, 2024**: $44.02 USD
- **Difference**: $4.19 USD (cheaper on November 22)

If you have any further questions or need assistance with booking, feel free to ask!

reviews.negative: Chargin the ev car was not easy…weren’t able to achieve that. I’m an ev user in uk but abroad is v different in terms of using a credit card.  More advice would be helpful, or some sort of pre-arranged registration to facilitate easier card payment.
reviews.positive: Love ev cars. It was very recent and had clever features my own etron didn’t have.

reviews.negative: Initially was offered a different car (Seat) but when explained we needed a bigger car, the staff scoffed and said it’s the same car before decided to give me the initial model I booked (Tiguan). Only wishing they would not switching customers car for no good reason.
reviews.positive: Excellent service. Staff were very attentive when explaining the rental rules and conditions. Clear explanation on the rules.

reviews.negative: Insurance costs were outrageous.
reviews.positive: Nice car, service was good.

reviews.negative:
My reservation was for Volkswagen Tiguan. 
The definition of this car category was:  MID size SUV with a capacity for 3 Large bags. 
Europcar gave me Cupra Formentor which is by any standard a small SUV or not an SUV at all.
If you look at the range of Cupra/Seat, the Ateca is the equivalent in size (mid SUV) and the Formentor is below it. 
Furthermore, There is absolutely no room for  3 Large bags (as reserved) in the Formentor.
I have pictures to support this.
Europcar were willing to change the car to station wagon to solve the 3 Large bags mismatch 
but this was not SUV and because I have a back problem, I need the SUV height.
They said they have no other SUV for me. 
So after a long flight I had no strength to continue to argue with them and I took the Formentor.
We had 3 Large bags so we drive with one of them in the cabin for 17 days!

- **Theft Excess**: €1,512.50
- **Damage Excess**: €1,512.50
- **Deposit**: €1,512.50

### Summary
Your friend can rent a Toyota Aygo from Avis at Amsterdam Schiphol Airport, with a total drive-away price of $172.25. The insurance package for full protection is available for $88.36, which includes comprehensive coverage. The supplier has a good reputation, with an overall rating of 8.7 based on customer reviews.

reviews.positive: It was very fortunate that I was given a bigger car than I had originally booked as the boot space was essential for our trip.
The customer service was impeccable, before and after collection/drop-off off the car.  The Avis representative game me an upgrade to European SUV and I couldn't have been more happier.
reviews.negative: Avis office, indeed car rental offices in general at Canberra airport, was not in the terminal and not the easiest to find.

reviews.positive: Upgraded several classes due to lack of availability!
reviews.negative: The car had a flat on pick-up

The car, a VW T-cross, had around 27,000km on the clock and the performance was less than expected. This could also have been the result of previous renters using 91 octane fuel instead of the 95 octane recommended by the manufacturers. The instrument data continually showed the left rear tyre below pressure despite being inflated to the required pressure by me and the NRMA. This was an unecessary worry.
reviews.positive: The seamless booking and ease of pick-up/drop off.
Speedy service, helpful staff, easy location, great economical car.
reviews.negative: No complaints!

reviews.negative:
Next to zero information on where to get picked up and taken to actual offsite depot. 
When called to find out the operator had no information and could not tell me where to get picked up from.
Booked the car with return time of 5am. Was informed at the time of pick up that they in fact are not open at 5am and didn’t have a shuttle bus service until 5:30am. To which I explained that was too late for my flight to which they just explained you can leave the car out the front and arrange an Uber to the airport. This is exactly what we did and despite several calls to confirm the car was left out the front and request someone to confirm they had it, 4 days later we are yet to receive confirmation or our deposit back. Will never book them again

The upgrade to a Ford Everest was a $8000 excess not the $5900 for the Pajero.
Europcar made it very clear they didn't recognise the insurance cover and made me doubt if I was covered or not.  In the end I paid an additional $800 for Europcar nil excess cover for peace of mind.  That in effect doubled the cost of the hire and was very poor value for money.
It felt like a scam!!!

The verbal FREE upgrade offered by agent Sybille, (due to a last-minute cancellation) was subsequently amended to a "choice upgrade' at an extra cost of CHF 74.28/day (x12 days), i.e. CHF 891.36 more than agreed through you. (that's C$1,488.57, i.e. 367% more than the basic rental prepaid through rentalcars.com!!! (that excessive rental cost noted above is exclusive of the 8.10% VAT, and the "Premium Location Fee" of 20%, which was not noted on the rentalcars.com agreement.  - not holding it against you....but SixT certainly lives up to its worldwide reputation as untrust-worthy rental company.
When they emailed me a request to rate their service, I told them loud and clear that unless they amend the final charge upon return of the vehicle, I'll see them in court.
The credit-card pre-authorization (Security Deposit) of CHF 1,463.56 was cancelled/withdrawn two days before end of rental, but to this day, I don't know what they debited to my credit-card, as there is still no Sixt debit showing on my Visa account.
That said, I had also purchased a CDW through rentalcoverage.com, the confirmation of which I showed to the SixT agent upon pickup (she did not take the details), but upon return of the vehicle they claimed that I damaged the rear-left wheel rim (5-10 cms down to primer); when I told the receiving agent that I a) have CDW coverage and b) had taken photos at time of pickup, which clearly shows the pre-existing damage, she noted it on the Return-Receipt, but I am now being hounded by the SixT-Damage dept. (As I'm still travelling, I have had no time to respond, and frankly see no reason why I should respond to that department.
Last, but not least, Sixt's Diamond member should not be permitted to push through a line of 12 people waiting to be served, when there is no dedicated Diamond-Member counter.
Decency toward the common-mortals is sorely lacking at Sixt!
PS: I've rented cars through rentalcars.com previously and everything went without a hitch....s
reviews.positive:
Originally, I appreciated the offer of a FREE upgrade to a BMW x2, however that pleasure was short-lived (see 'what you didn't like').
This slightly larger vehicle was good to drive, but had useless gadgets which made driving in darkness outright dangerous. I did like the automatic transmission and the heads-up display, though. The fuel-mileage was great too.
The SIXT rental desk is easily located and car condition is good
reviews.negative: The SIXT representative keen to push me to upgrade my car (which required CHF 50 per day) and insurance.  After my rejection, I was  told to wait 30min as my booked needed more time to do cleaning.  I booked the car at 2pm; I finally got the car (same size/group; but not my )
The gas tank was not completely full.  Not quite what I expected from Sixt.
The cost of additional full protection of insurance is quite high
reviews.positive: Sixt is my rental car choice

reviews.negative: Every time I buy a car from this company, they tell a lie that you must have a credit card and you cannot rent a car with a debit card unless you buy full insurance from us.

Also booking.com cancelled my original booking due to me being late. However, I had put my flight details into the app to make sure that didn’t happen like requested.
